Citation.sTitle: Thermo-physical properties of 1,3,4-oxadiazole derivatives in pure solvents
Citation.sAbstract: A systematic thermo-physical characterization of the two compounds 2-((4-acetyl-5-(4-methoxyphenyl)-  5-methyl-4,5-dihydro-1,3,4-oxadiazol-2-yl)methylthio)-3-o-tolylquinazolin-4(3H)-one (PDI-A)  and 2-((4-acetyl-5-methyl-5-p-tolyl-4,5-dihydro-1,3,4-oxadiazol-2-yl)methylthio)-3-o-tolylquinazolin-  4(3H)-one (PDI-G) in two different solvents viz. chloroform (CF) and N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF) were  elucidated. Thus, density (q), viscosity (g) and ultrasonic sound velocity (U) and thereby various acoustical  and thermodynamic parameters have been determined over the range of T = (303, 308, and 313) K  and at atmospheric pressure. Moreover, a comparison between experimental results for the pure solvents  and solutions of compound PDI-A and compound PDI-G studied has been carried out to analyze carefully  how the structural modifications affect the values of Gibbs energy of activation (DG), enthalpy of activation  (DH) and entropy of activation (DS) in CF and DMF.
